Software limit switches "I_DisbaleSoftwareLimitSwitches" :
The software limit switches are programmed before the hardware limit switches. This will give the drive the possiblility to decelarate accordingly as its knows the distance to these SW LS's from the encoder value.
When the referencing is ok it should be impossible to reach the hardware limit switches. Only when there is a faulty referencing then the software limit switches can be behind the hardware limit switch. In that case it is possible to hit the hardware limit switch with full speed.
Positive <-- Load --> negative HW LS SW LS _____ SW LS HW LS ____ ____ l_____l ____ ____ l____\ l____\ l_____l /____l /____l OOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO ll // \\ ll ll// \\ll ll ll
************************************************************************************
